On my end only these rules seems to be required:
```adblock
kisstvshow.net,lifestylehack.info,keephealth.info,kimcartoon.li,kissorg.net,kisstvshow.to,kissasian.*#@$##divContentVideo { display: block !important; }
kisstvshow.net,lifestylehack.info,keephealth.info,kimcartoon.li,kissorg.net,kisstvshow.to,kissasian.*#@$?##centerDivVideo > div[id]:not(#divContentVideo):not(:has(video)) { remove: true; }
```
So I guess that we can add directive like:
```adblock
!#if (adguard_app_windows || adguard_app_mac || adguard_app_android || adguard_ext_chromium || adguard_ext_opera)
kisstvshow.net,lifestylehack.info,keephealth.info,kimcartoon.li,kissorg.net,kisstvshow.to,kissasian.*#$?##centerDivVideo > div[id]:not(#divContentVideo):not(:has(video)) { remove: true; }
kisstvshow.net,lifestylehack.info,keephealth.info,kimcartoon.li,kissorg.net,kisstvshow.to,kissasian.*#$##divContentVideo { display: block !important; }
!#endif
```
